task.summary: Default task
Markers now find label from input data for colour without manual input. Added plot to show quantisation errors and frequency of neuron activation

converted conditionals for finding input data labels into list comprehension - much more elegant. Fixed error with plotting Banbury data by transposing for sklearn to normlaise and plotting the transpose of that.
fixed hexagonal topology for plotting
full script for rectangular topology including SOM, SOM with scatter chart, frequency of node activation, and quantisation error
naming convention
naming convention
rectangular topology
figure legends and titles
Started TDD for banbury data extraction and file processing
testing cwd manipulations
revamped banbury.py and test_banbury.py with classes and full TDD
finished banbury.py to convert all banbury data into format i can use with mysom module. this production was performed using TDD, and so is robust.

Now that the Banbury data are usable, I am running my som code on them to investigate how changing SOM parameters affects the results. This code still needs to be refactored into an importable module.
initiated the idea of a scatter plot threshold, k, such that points are only plotted overlaying SOM neurons which were activated at least k times
attempted k threshold for scatter diagram with prostate cell line data

MySOM module now fully integratable, just needs work on density plot. I realised that there ws a transposition error in the skleran normalisation method, now resolved, which gives much better delineation of SOM groups.
directory restructured
Plot refactoring so that all plots have a hidden or unhidden legend box - this makes constraints uniform across plots
Unblinding of data for experiment 1
Investigating dense regions and outlying data.
